ongressional District. NY Times<p><li>10/29/96 <a href="http://interactive6.wsj.com/archive/retrieve@4.cgi?geneb5/text/wsjie/data/SB846547716207820000.djm/&NVP=&template=news-search.tmpl&form=news-search.html&dbname=wsjie%2Findex&dbname=autowire%2Findex&words=tobacco&any-all=AND&maxitems=30&HI=30"> Why Tobacco Lobby Is Backing Alternative Medicine Measure</a> Acupuncture and Smoking align. WSJ<p><li>10/28/96<a href="http://interactive6.wsj.com/archive/retrieve@4.cgi?geneb5/text/wsjie/data/SB846460505478185500.djm/&NVP=&template=news-search.tmpl&form=news-search.html&dbname=wsjie%2Findex&dbname=autowire%2Findex&words=tobacco&any-all=AND&maxitems=30&HI=30 "> Enticing Cigar Ads Leave Smokers Unaware of Risks</a> WSJ<p><li>10/28/96 <a href="http://interactive6.wsj.com/archive/retrieve@4.cgi?geneb5/text/autowire/data/BT-CO-19961029-3858.djml/&NVP=&template=news-search.tmpl&form=news-search.html&dbname=wsjie%2Findex&dbname=autowire%2Findex&words=tobacco&any-all=AND&maxitems=30&HI=30"> Smoking Foes Plan Attempt To Toughen Warning Labels</a> WSJ<p><li>10/28/96 <a href="http://www.sportsline.com:80/u/sportsticker/html/collegebasketball/LGNS/BKC--COCHCANCER-X.HTM"> Coaches vs. Cancer Council Focuses on Tobacco</a> From SportsLine USA<p><li>10/27/96 <a href="http://www1.nytimes.com/yr/mo/day/news/notnyt/smoking-cancer-review.html"> So, Smoking Causes Cancer. This is News?</a> How the recent molecular link makes the dangers more concrete for some; while many "may never be persuaded." NY Times<p><li>10/28/96 <a href="http://foxnews.com/news/wires/n_1028_120.sml">  Japanese Smoking Hits Record Low</a> Rates for males and females lowest since 1965.  AP thru Fox news<p><li>10/28/96 <a href="http://foxnews.com/news/wires/n_1025_18.sml"> Tenn. Tobacco Farmers Cautioned on Migrant Hiring</a> AP thru Fox News<P><li>10/27/96 <a href="http://www2.phillynews.com:80/inquirer/96/Oct/27/city/WOES27.htm"> Smoking Merits for Parkas</a> Philadelphia Inquirer<p><li>10/25/96 <a href="http://times.st-pete.fl.us:80/News2/102596/BUSINESS/Restaurants__bars_opp.html"> National Bar/Restaurant Group Opposes Tobacco Regulation--Uses PM Money to Fund Survey</a> National Licensed Beverage Association takes stand against OSHA. St. Petersburg Times<p><li>10/25/96 <a href="http://www.irish-times.com:80/irish-times/paper/1025/for4.html"> British Doctor Blames Mothers for Cot Death</a> A bitter storm breaks out in UK medicine.  <i>Dr Simpson concluded that it was the mother rather than the smoke that was to blame. Mothers who smoke "tend to be impulsive and have been described as arousal-seeking extroverts", he wrote.</i> Irish Times<p><li><a href="http://yourhealthdaily.com:80/297_102396_094002_22597.html"> Smoking and Tooth Loss Study</a> Your Health Daily<p><li>10/23/96 <a href="http://washingtonpost.com:80/wp-srv/WPlate/1996-10/23/066L-102396-idx.html"> MD: Restaurants Hit With Civil Rights Complaints on Behalf of Those With Respiratory Ailments</a> Wash. Post<p><li>10/23/96 <a href="http://washingtonpost.com:80/wp-srv/WPlate/1996-10/23/048L-102396-idx.html"> Nicotine Prevents Alzheimer's-related Plaque in Test Tube</a> Beneficial effects of nictoine on Alzheimers? Washington Post<p><li>10/23/96 <a href="http://www.chron.com:80/content/chronicle/business/96/10/23/smoke.2-0.html"> Woman Files Sex/Smoking Suit</a> Clerk says men allowed to smoke, but she was fired</a> Houston Chronicle<p><li>10/22/96 <a href="http://www.bnet.att.com/leadstories/96-10-22/index.htm"> Can the Tobacco Idustry Take the Heat?</a> Compilation of articles by Lead Story<p><li>10/21/96 <a href="http://interactive4.wsj.com/edition/current/articles/SB845852984730798500.htm"> Tobacco Industry May Change Tactics Due to Cigarette/Cancer Link</a> WSJ, if you're subscribed<p><li>10/20/96 <a href="http://www.nytimes.com:80/yr/mo/day/news/national/tobacco-exclusive.html"> Tobacco Fights Market-priced Cigs in Military</a>  All 12 members of the House National Security Committee's oversight panel on military morale, welfare and recreation have demanded that the Pentagon cancel a Nov. 1 rollback of the  subsidy of tobacco products sold in commissaries. Surprise: 11 of the 12 have gotten money from tobacco PACs over the last two years. From the NY Times. You can check out <a href="http://www.house.gov/nsc/welcome.htm"> House National Security Committee's HomePage</a> but there's not much there on it--yet.<p><li>10/21/96 <a href="http://wire.nj.com/cgi-bin/lmc/hlview.pl?/disk04/wire/AP/Stream-Parsed/GENERAL/a0667_AM_OutFront-SilverSmokes"> Fewer Americans Smoke, But Hollywood Can't Kick Habit</a> Smoking in Movies unchanged in 3 decades. From AP. If not there, then <a href="http://www2.phillynews.com:80/inquirer/96/Oct/21/national/SMOK21.htm">The Philadelphia Inquirer</a><p>10/20/96 <a href="http://www.cnnfn.com:80/hotstories/economy/9610/18/tobacco_pkg/"> Tobacco interests back Republicans heavily in a fight over their industry </a> CNN<p><li>10/18/96<a href="http://www.nytimes.com:80/yr/mo/day/news/national/ny-tobacco.html"> NYC Sues Tobacco Cos</a> NY Times<p><li>10/18/96 <a href="http://www.businessweek.com:80/1996/44/b3499127.htm"> PM to Spin Off Tobacco, Divide it into Foreign and Domestic Ops?</a> Business Week on the rumors.<p><li>10/18/96 <a href="http://www.businessweek.com:80/1996/44/b3499161.htm"> Ready to Quit Yet?</a> A report on cessation clinics/methods. Business Week<p><li>10/18/96 <a href="http://www.smokescreen.org/sfaction/index.htm"> Tobacco Report Card Issued!</a> And Voter's Guide. Wow. A state-by-state tally of the 104th Congress--who's taking tobacco money and who's fighting tobacco control bills! Someone's gonna get spanked. A bombshell from Pennsylvania's new SmokeFree Action. <p><li>10/17/96 <a href="http://www.cnn.com/HEALTH/9610/17/nfm/smoking.gun/index.htm"> Tobacco Carcinogen Directly Linked to Lung Cancer DNA Mutation</a>  Benzo (a) pyrene shown to damage lung cancer-specific "hotspot" on P53 gene. Layman's report from CNN.<br> See the story on the new <a href="http://wire.ap.org/APpackages/smoking/index.html"> AP NewsWire</a><br> Or read the full<a href="http://www.sciencemag.org:80/science/scripts/display/full/274/5286/430.html"> Science Magazine article</a><br> 10/18/96 PBS Online Newshour features <a href="http://www1.pbs.org:80/newshour/bb/health/october96/cancer_10-18.html">A good layman's explanation plus a deeper meaning:</a> now we may be able to identify and find other disease-causing agents' "fingerprints."<p><li>10/16/96 <a href="http://www.seattletimes.com:80/extra/browse/html/altsmok_101696.html"> Parents Learning to Keep their Secondhand Smoke out of Their Children's Lungs</a> From Frank Blethen's Seattle Times<p><li> 10/15/96 <strong><a href="http://www.smokescreen.org/sfaction/index.htm"> Tobacco Report Card Issued!!</a></strong> State-by-state tally of the 104th Congress--who's taking tobacco money and who's fighting tobacco control legislation! <br>A bombshell from SmokeFree Action. <br><a href="http://www.wsj.com">WSJ</a> has it, if you're subscribed<p><li>10/7/96 <a href="http://www.tobacco.neu.edu/Extra/hotdocs/memo2destroy.htm">Young & Rubicam 1991 Memo on Destroying Joe Camel Research</a> From the Tobacco Litigation Project<li>10/16/96 <a href="http://washingtonpost.com:80/wp-srv/WPlate/1996-10/16/114L-101696-idx.html">Friendship Heights, MD, Council Bans Smoking Indoors--and Out</a> Washington Post<p><li>10/15/96: <a href="http://www.chron.com:80/content/chronicle/nation/96/10/16/scotus.html">Supreme Court Holds Warning Labels Shield Industry</a> Court Disallows Texas Smoker's Suit. Smoking's dangers "have long been known to the community," court rules. Houston Chronicle (You'll have to Register first)<p><li>10/15/96 <a href="http://www2.phillynews.com:80/inquirer/96/Oct/16/national/CIG16.htm">KY, NC File for Summary Judgement against FDA</a> Philiadelphia Inquirer<p><li>10/15/96 <a href="http://www.msnbc.com:80/news/34876.asp">Nicotine Patch/Gum Dangers</a> It's still a dangerous drug. Be smart. Use cautiously. MSNBC<p><li><a href="http://www.herring.com:80/mag/issue36/points.html"> Web Co. Wooed to Build Smokers' Sites</a> EXERPT from a Red Herring article on advertising on the web: <i> . . . one senses that as they become more familiar with the medium, advertisers will become much more subtle in the ways they incorporate their pitches into content. Certainly, this kind of approach could serve the interests of companies like Philip Morris that have been shut out of other media. Josh Greer, president of Digital Planet, an interactive marketing firm, says that his company was approached by an Asian tobacco conglomerate and several US tobacco companies to build community-based Web sites for smokers. Digital Planet refused these very rich offers as a matter of principle. </i><p><li><a href="http://www.hookup.net/~tpolevoy/hildawilson.html">Shopper's Drug Mart, Imasco and the Ontario Lung Association</a> What a crew! But Dr. Terry Polevoy's on the case about this and other strange Canadian bedfellows.<p><li>10/14/96: <a href="http://152.160.1.36:80/STRAT/9610/14/workp/workp.htm">OSHA Proposals Fought by ex-OSHA Head</a> Detroit News on Patrick Tyson's lobbying for Philip Morris.<li>10/7/96 <a href="http://www.iguide.com:80/tv/magazine/961007/style.sml">Female TV Stars Take up Cigars</a> "Must Smoke TV" TV Guide<li>10/14/96: <a href="http://www.barrons.com"> Barron's Cover Story on Carter Case Lawyer Norwood Wilner </a> All about Woody. You'll need to register (free for now).<li>10/11/96: In the Sept/Oct Mother Jones:<ul><li>Check out Wisconsin's favorite activist son, <strong>Ira Sharenow, </strong> in <a href="http://www.motherjones.com:80/mother_jones/SO96/hellraiser.html"> Hellraiser Central</a> <li> And in <a href="http://www.motherjones.com:80/mother_jones/SO96/brokaw.html">Tobacco Loves NY,</a> MoJo covers the inside story of <strong>Gov. Pataki's</strong> refusal to allow the Health Comminssioner to criticize a "pre-emption" bill that would have gutted existing smokefree air laws.<li>And if you want to make a federal case out of it, <a href="http://bsd.mojones.com/mother_jones/SO96/dozen.html"> The Dirty Dozen</a> of the 104th Congress has, of course, some tobacco material.</ul><li>10/10/96: <a href="http://www.smh.com.au:80/daily/content/1996/Oct/10/pageone/961010-pageone4.html">Are cigarette packs advertising? Even in a tobacco store??</a> Read about the astounding Supreme Court decision in Sydney, Australia<li>10/3/96:<a href="http://www.nejm.org:80/publicM/1996/0335/0014/1077a/1.htm">The Doctor-Activist: Physicians fighting for social change</a> A book review in the Oct. 3 NEJM. One of the physicians profiled is Dr. Judith Mackay, who has fought tobacco in Asia--despite Bob Dole--for years.<li>10/9/96: <a href="http://washingtonpost.com:80/wp-srv/WPlate/1996-10/09/055L-100996-idx.html">Smoke Gets in Your Eyes, Blinding You</a> Study links smoking & macular degeneration; from the Washington Post<li>10/10/96: <a href="http://www.nytimes.com:80/yr/mo/day/news/national/teens-marijuana.html"> Teen-Agers Find Drugs Easy to Obtain and Warnings Easy to Ignore </a> NY Times<li>10/5/96: <a href="http://www.improb.com"> The IgNobel Awards</a> from the Annals of Improbable Medicine. 7 tobacco companies won an Iggie for their discovery, announced in 1994 before Congress, that nicotine is not addictive!<li>10/2/96: 1964 "smoking gun" report made public by Rep. Martin T. Meehan (D-Mass.). See the <a href="http://washingtonpost.com:80/wp-srv/WPlate/1996-10/02/125L-100296-idx.html"> Washington Post story,</a> or read the actual : <a href="http://www.gate.net/~jcannon/documents/6410ind1.txt"> REPORTS ON POLICY ASPECTS OF THE SMOKING AND HEALTH SITUATIONS IN U.S.A.</a> by two British tobacco company researchers who came to the US, met and reported on all the major players, and told of a high-level "policy committee" made up of attorneys of all six tobacco companies. An historic inside snapshot and a revelation.<li>10/8/96: <a href="http://www.cnnfn.com:80/hotstories/companies/9610/08/amerbrands/"> American Brands to Abandon Tobacco Ship? </a> AMB Making Plans to Spin off Gallahers Unit<li>10/04/96: EU Commissioner Flynn calls for public recognition of tobacco's toll, and an end to advertising. Blasts sports, movie stars.</strong>  See the latest developments at the Helsinki "Smoking or Health" conference at the brand-new <a href="http://europa.eu.int/en/comm/dg05/tobacco/index.html"> European Network for Smoking Prevention WebSite</a> (This link requires an authorization(!), but meanwhile, here's <a href="http://www.uicc.ch/events/helsinki/"> full info on EU Tobacco or Health Conference</a><p><li>November's <strong><a href="http://www.fairfieldweekly.com/">Good Housekeeping</a></strong> has a special <strong>"Safety Alert"</strong> on secondhand smoke.<br>(Not on their site yet.)<br><i>Extra Added Bonus! No Tobacco Ads. None. Zero. Zip.</i><p><li>This Week's <strong> Fairfield County (CT) Weekly</a></strong> features <strong><a href="http://www.fairfieldweekly.com/articles/smoke.html"> Smoke Screen,</a></strong> about the industry's setting up of "watchdog" groups. <br><i>Extra Added Bonus! No Tobacco Ads. None. Zero. Zip.</i><p><li> The <strong>New Republic's</strong> cover story, <a href="http://www.enews.com/magazines/tnr/current/gladwell110496.html"> Freedom's Smoke</a> features an industry-sympathetic multi-tobacco-book review by Malcolm Gladwell. After reading "Smokescreen," "Ashes to Ashes," and, uh, "The Runaway Jury," and after taking Viscusi's dismissal of ETS risks at face value, Gladwell agrees with Kluger's proposal to settle with the industry: <i> . . .   addiction is a disease. . . Diseases are not criminal enterprises. They demand treatment, not protection. </i> </center><HR><address><br>***********************   <li>©1996 <a href=mailto:geneb@dx.com>G