<center><h3>NYC ALERT! </h3>
<strong>EFFIE Awards Protest Wednesday 5PM</strong></center>
<br><strong>INFACT</strong> and the <strong>Coalition for a Smoke-free City</strong> will protest the <strong>American Marketing Association's</strong> induction of Philip Morriss' <strong> Marlboro Man</strong> into the <strong>Advertising Hall of Fame</strong> at the EFFIE Awards ceremony.  INFACT will be on hand with the <strong>Human Toll of Tobacco</strong>, a collection of hundreds of photos of people who have died or suffer from tobacco-related illnesses.  The photos will be displayed on a 200-foot banner.
<blockquote>WHEN:  <strong>Wednesday,</strong> June 5, <strong>5:00 p.m.</strong>
<br>WHERE: <strong>Marriott Marquis</strong> Hotel
<br>1535 Broadway at 45th Street
<br>New York City, NY
</blockquote>
