<h3><center>VCR Alerts</h3></center>


<li>4/15/96. "Ashes to Ashes" received a postitive review from Christopher Lehman-Haupt in the New York Times: <i>What is perhaps most disturbing about reading this minutely detailed volume - at least to someone who smoked his way through three decades of Kluger's 100-year history - is to learn how completely manipulated one was. Not only is ``Ashes to Ashes'' another report of the banality of evil, it is also an exercise in horrifying nostalgia.</i>
<li><strong><i>Smoke in the Eye,</i> FRONTLINE, PBS, April 2nd, 1996, 9pm ET </strong> Watch for Repeats
<br><strong>PLUS--A Web Special: <i>CIGARETTE PAPERS--A DOCUDRAMA IN THREE ACTS</strong> </strong> 
<br>On April 2nd, <a href="http://www.pbs.org/frontline/">Frontline </a> introduced a Web-based drama through hyperlinks to internal tobacco company documents posted on the Internet. Features include:

<ul><li>Interviews with newsmedia figures, including Walter Cronkite and Mike Wallace;
<li>Full-text articles on the ABC/CBS run-ins with the tobacco industry
<li><a href="http://www.pbs.org/frontline/smoke/links/"><i>Tobacco on the Web,</i></a> a guided tour to additional WWW information</ul>
<p>
<li><strong>Month-long trial on <i>Gerry Spence, </i> CNBC-TV,  starting Sat, March 23, 1996</strong>
<br> The U.S. Congress and the tobacco industry is being tried for "genocidal conspiracy" in a special 4-week series on <i>Gerry Spence </i> The CNBC-TV show began Sat, March 23 at 7:30 pm ET. The program will be repeated Sat at 11:30 pm and again on Sun, March 24th at 7:30 pm and 11:30 pm. In the month-long mock trial, famed lawyer Spence makes opening arguments week 1, hears from witnesses durings weeks 2 & 3, and comes to judgement on week 4.
<br><strong><center>YOU can be a witness--Call [1-800-752-CNBC]. </strong></center></i>

