<!--End of Sequential Linkers-->
<center><h2>The Richard Kluger 5-Point Peace Plan</h2>
Excerpts from the April 7, 1996 New York Times Magazine article <i>Dance with the Devil</i></center>
<hr>
<br>...feel-good moralizing and name-calling fail to advance the true social imperative the issue demands: saving as many as possible of the more than 400,000 lives smoking takes annually in this country. . .  it is time . . . to make a deal--to dance with the devil. . .

<p>All sides, accordingly, may find this  to be an auspicious time to consider a sweeping legislative compromise, embracing the following features:

<ol>
<li>CONGRESS WOULD ISSUE A BLANKET GRANT OF IMMUNITY TO THE TOBACCO COMPANIES AGAINST ALL PENDING AND FUTURE PRODUCT-LIABILITY CLAIMS ON THE GROUNDS THAT THE HIGHLY HAZARDOUS NATURE OF SMOKING HAS BEEN COMMON KNOWLEDGE AND ADEQUATELY WARNED AGAINST.</li> 
<p>
<li>THE FDA WOULD BE GIVEN REGULATORY OVERSIGHT OF MANUFACTURE AND PACKAGING OF CIGARETTES, INCLUDING THE POWER TO SET MAXIMUM LEVELS FOR THEIR HAZARDOUS INCREDIENTS.</li> 
<p>
<li>HEALTH WARNING LABELS WOULD BE ENLARGED TO OCCUPY THE ENTIRE BACK OF ALL CIGARETTE PACKS AND WOULD CARRY FAR MORE INFORMATIVE LANGUAGE.</li> 
<p>
<li>PROMPT IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PROPOSED OSHA REGULATION RESTRICTING SMOKING AT MOST WORK PLACES TO WELL-VENTILATED ANNEXES AND OF THE FDA PROGRAM TO MAKE CIGARETTE MARKETING FAR LESS ALLURING TO YOUNG PEOPLE.</li> 
<p>
<li>THE FEDERAL CIGARETTE TAX WOULD BE DOUBLED TO 48 CENTS TO PAY FOR ENFORCING THESE NEW REGULATIONS. AN ADDITIONAL 2-CENTS-A-PACK LEVY WOULD PAY FOR AN ANTISMOKING ADVERTISING CAMPAIGN AND OTHER PUBLIC EDUCATION PROGRAMS LIKE FREE QUIT CLINICS, TO BE RUN BY THE OFFICE ON SMOKING AND HEALTH.</li> 
</ol>
<br>
Such a five-point settlement . . . could save thousands of lives and go far toward reducing the severest effects of an infernal product that as a practical matter can never be outlawed or ever made truly safe.


<HR><address>
