-----------------------------------------------------------------
A DEFENSE OF TABACCO
Roger Marbecke (London, 1602)
   "It is good for scurvy, for weake cold stomakes ... for grosse and soggy bodies," Roger Marbecke of London wrote in the 1602 book "A Defence of Tabacco," on file in a Washington library, its pages as brownish-yellow as a nicotine-stained finger.

