"Preventing Tobacco Use Among Young People," 1994

U.S. Oepartment of Health and Human Services Report to Congress "Smoking and Health: A National Status Report." 2nd edition, 1990

-----------------------------------------------------------------

THE LAST PUFF, Ex-smokers Share the Secrets of their Success
Edited by John W. Farquhar, MD and Gene A. Spiller, PhD
Published in 1990 by W.W. Norton & Co. 500 Fifth Ave., NY, NY 10110
ISBN: 0-393-30803-0 Featuring testimony from 30 ex-smokers, including ex-Winston Man David Goerlitz, and Patrick Reynolds--RJ Reynolds' grandson who, unlike Doris Duke, invested his inheritance in helping others fight their addiction to tobacco.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
"If only I could Quit"
Karen Casey of the Hazelden Meditation Series
ISBN:0-06-255455-7

It contains 2 main parts.  Part I is a series of ex-smokers relating their
struggle / strategies / experiences to quit smoking.  Part II is a series
of daily thoughts for a 3 month period to reflect on the process of quitting.

My favorite book however is 
-----------------------------------------------------------------
"You can stop smoking"
Jacquelyn Rogers.
Pocket Book ISBN 0-671-70295-5.

-----------------------------------------------------------------

Chandler's Invisible Hand or his Scale and Scope that discuss the industry.  

-----------------------------------------------------------------

The Bureau of Corporation reports are probably the most informative works available on the industry early in this century.  It seems my estimation of "many helpful publications" a little inflated.

Burns, Malcolm R. 1982. 
"Outside Intervention in Monopolitistic Price Warfare: The Case of the `Plug War' and Union Tobacco Company." 
Business History Review 56(1):33-53.

1983. "Economics of Scale of Tobacco Manufacture, 1897-1910."
Journal of Economic History 43(1):461-85.

1989. "New Evidence on Predatory Price Cutting." 
Managerial and Decision Economics 10(4):327-30.

