<META HTTP-EQUIV="copyright" content="Copyight 1995 Gene Borio,
<META NAME="keywords" content="tobacco">
<META NAME="keywords" content="smoking">
<META NAME="keywords" content="information ">
<META NAME="distribution" content=global>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Reply-to" content=cdtlbrew@aol.com>
<META NAME="Reply-to" content=cdtlbrew@aol.com>
</HEAD>
<!--Sequential Linkers--
<!--End of Sequential Linkers-->

<h3>NEWS FROM B.A.R.T. </h3>

<p> <BR>B.A.R.T. ENTERPRISES <BR>2800 N. BELTLINE BLVD. <BR>COLUMBIA, SC  29204

<P>Press Contact: Chris Barutha  803/790-0947 or <a href=mailto:cdtlbrew@aol.com>cdtlbrew@aol.com</a>

<h3>SMOKING IS NO LONGER A DIRTY HABIT WITH NIC NAP </h3>

<p>B.A.R.T. Enterprises has developed a new product called Nic Nap to eliminate nicotine stain and smell from smokers hands.      </p>

<p>Chris Barutha, B.A.R.T. president, said "Nic Nap is a product and a service that smokers can purchase.  The government, the media, and everyone else was out to get smokers.  We decided to produce a product that would satisfy smokers and the rest of the world as well.   Most people don't want to smell badly and Nic Nap is simply a product for people who care.  It's convenient, easy to use, and sensible."</p>

<p>Why use Nic Nap?    </p>

<p>With increased pressure from non-smokers, smokers have been banned to the great outdoors to enjoy their habit. Naturally, more of the cigarette that previously burned in an ashtray, is now burning in the hands of the smoker.  "Smokers are now holding the cigarette the entire time they are smoking it.  Where else are they going to put it when they are standing outside?", asked Barutha.   Nic Nap addresses this concern created by legislation and company policies.  It provides smoking consumers with a solution, a product designed with the intent to specifically eliminate their problem.                      </p>
<p>B.A.R.T. said  the cost will vary as to how consumers wish to purchase Nic Nap. It will be offerred at bulk rates to companies who wish to provide them for their employees, while consumers will be able to purchase packs of five and ten with pocket change. They said "regardless how you wish to purchase Nic Nap, it will be affordable".</p>

<p>"Nic Nap allows a smoker to fight back to the criticism they receive", B.A.R.T.'s Barutha stressed.  "This is the answer for women, business people, and whomever wants their hands to smell fresh at their own convenience."</p>
                                                          
                                                           #

<p>(Nic Nap is a registered trademark)</p>

<p>Contact:</p>

<BR>Chris Barutha <BR>B.A.R.T.  Enterprises <BR>President, Communications and Public Affairs <BR>2800 N. Beltline Blvd. <BR>Columbia, SC  29204

<BR>803/790-0947  or cdtlbrew@aol.com

