rd was given to New York City Mayor Rudolph Giuliani for his individual efforts to improve lung health of his constituents and visitors to New York through a ban on smoking in restaurants and public buildings.*1996, the Partnering for World Health Award was received by attorneys general of Mississippi, Arizona and Oklahoma for their activities in filing lawsuits against tobacco companies to recover taxpayer costs of treating smoking-related disease.American Council on Science and Health (ACSH)Dr. Elizatbeth Whelan1995 Broadway, 2nd FlNew York, NY  10023-5860(212) 362-7044(212) 362-4919*Priorities (Magazine)American Dental Association211 East Chicago AvenueChicago, IL  60611(312) 440-2500*Warning: Smokeless Tobacco Can Cause Mouth Cancer*ADA CatalogueAmerican Health Association7320 Greenville AvenueDallas, TX  75231(214) 822-9380*Calling It Quits*Guidelines for Weight ControlAmerican Health Foundation320 E. 43rd StreetNew York, NY  10017American Heart Association7320 Greenville AvenueDallas, TX  75231(214) 822-9380(800) 527-6941American Heart Association (DC)1250 Connecticut Ave., N.W.Washington, DC  20036(202) 822-9380American Lung Association1740 BroadwayNew York, NY  10019-4374(212) 315-8700*Freedom From Smoking*Stop Smoking Stay TrimAmerican Medical Association Division Of C535 North Dearborn StreetChicago, IL  60610(312) 645-4419American Nonsmokers Assn32 Glenwood Ave.Newton, MA  02159Americans For A Smoke-Free SocietySidney Ayscue2175 Lenox Road NE, Suite A-7Atlanta, GA  30324(404) 299-2604Americans For Nonsmokers RightsJulia Carol Co-Director2530 San Pablo Ave., Ste. JBerkeley, CA  94702(510) 841-3032(510) 841-7702Andrews' Tobacco Industry Litigation Reporter Tomas Hennessey, EditorP.O. Box 1000Westtown, PA 19395(800) 345-1101tmhenesy@voicenet.comArgentine League for Combating Cancer*Organizers of "Clean Air Day" 3rd Thu. of Nov.Arizona Smokers' HelplineArizona Program for Nicotine