hypnotherapy; seminars (3-6 persons), semi-private(2 persons) and private programs available. Free 90-day support and reinforcement. Fee: $95-$250.GREEN SEMINARS, 883-3232 or (800) 342-1303. Holds 2-hour sessions at local hospitals; 1st hour free orientation, 2nd hour group hypnosis, tapes and educational material provided. In Nassau: Long Island Jewish Medical Center, North Shore University, Massapequa GeneralHospital, South Nassau Communities Hospital. In Suffolk: Brookhaven Memorial Hospital, Southside Hospital, John T. Mather Hospital, Community Hospital of Western Suffolk and Eastern Long Island Hospital. Fee: $60.GROUP AGAINST SMOKING POLLUTION (GASP), 7 Maxine Ave., Plainview; 938-0080.Information on smoking cessation, advocacy efforts for smoking restrictions. For newsletter, send stamped, self-addressed envelope. Fee: None.THE NEW CENTER FOR WHOLISTIC HEALTH EDUCATION AND RESEARCH, 6801Jericho Tpk., Syosset; (800) 922-7337. Smoking cessation program using acupuncture, offered at least twice yearly; includes lecture on benefits of acupuncture, aftercare, breathing exercises, videoon effects of smoking, tapes and other educational material. Fee: $300; no fee if 2nd clinic is needed; $100 afterwards.STOP SMOKING CENTER, Selden; 698-7760. Call for location; 5-day behavioral modification program and aversion therapy. Fee: $295. HOSPITAL PROGRAMS: Long Beach Memorial, Long Beach, 897-1000.  Behavioral educational program; fee $375, includes 8-week quit sessions and 6-month maintenance program. Mercy Medical Center, Rockville Centre; 255-2435. I Quit Club behavior modification, self-help group, meets Mondays; no fee. North Shore University, Manhasset; 926-8831. Kick the Habit is a single 2-hour session including counseling, hypnosis, behavior modification, tapes, educational material; $60, meetings once a month. St. Francis, Roslyn; 938-0080. Stop Smoking Clinic includes a 7-session program, 2 hours each session, and a monthly reinforcement meeting (can be used in conjunction with nicotine patches), with group interaction, pulmonary function test to detect lung damage, films, audio cassettes, 24-hour hotline and guest speakers; fee $125, includes life membership in I Quit Club; 1st session free. Winthrop-University, Mineola; 663-2579. Behavioral modification, Freedom From Smoking group, 4 sessions; fee $60.</PRE><HR><address><br>***********************<li>©1995 <a href=mailto:geneb@tobacco.org>Gene Borio</a>, the Tobacco BBS  (212-982-4645. WebPage: http://www.tobacco.org.)</li> <li>Original Tobacco  BBS material may be reprinted in any non-commercial venue if accompanied by this credit line. </li> </address><br>***********************<br><a href=http://www.tobacco.org>Return to Tobacco BBS HomePage</a><br>***********************<p>END OF DOCUMENT</p></HTML>
