rell</strong></li> <li><strong>Williams, Samuel Clay</strong></li><li><strong>Wills, 1st baron</strong></li><li><strong>Wills, William</strong></li> <li><strong>Wilson, Don W.</strong></li> <li><strong>Wilson, J. Tyler</strong></li> <li><strong>Wilson, Pete</strong></li> <li><strong>Woessner, Anna F.</strong></li><li><strong>Wolfe, Sidney</strong></li> <li><strong>Wolfner, Benedict</strong></li><li><strong>Woodbery, Daniel Hoyt</strong></li><li><strong>Wright, J. Skelly</strong></li> <li><strong>Wright, Jim</strong></li> <li><strong>Wurman, Harry Paul</strong></li><li><strong>Wyden, Ron</strong></li> <li><strong>Wynder, Ernst L.</strong></li> <p>Y<p><li><strong>Ybor, Vicente Martinez</strong> 1818-1896; Ybor City, FL</li><li><strong>Yeaman, Addison </strong> d. July 7, 1996 in Louisville at the age of 88. General Counsel of B&W from 1954 to 1972</li> </li> <li><strong>Yellen, Manuel</strong></li> <li><strong>Yesner, Raymond</strong></li> <li><strong>Yeutter, Clayton K.</strong></li> <li><strong>Yuille, Thomas Burks</strong></li><p>Z<p><li><strong>Zahn, Leonard</strong></li> <li><strong>Zelkowitz, David</strong></li> <li><strong>Zeller, Mitch</strong></li> <li><strong>Zemer, Charles</strong></li> <li><strong>Zimmerman, Dennis</strong> Economist who wrote, with Gravelle, a 1994 critique of the 1993 EPA secondhand smoke report</li> </ul><HR><address><br>***********************   <li>©1996 <a href=mailto:geneb@dx.com>Gene Borio,</a> Tobacco BBS (212-982-4645). WebPage: <a href=" http://www.tobacco.org">  http://www.tobacco.org).</a>Original Tobacco BBS material may be reprinted in any non-commercial venue if accompanied by this credit </li> </address><br>***********************<br><a href=http://www.tobacco.org>Return to Tobacco BBS HomePage</a><br>***********************<p>END OF DOCUMENT</p></HTML>list
