 in Support of Summary Judgement"</A> The PM Memo ABC Never Got to Show. On the use of nicotine in the manufacture of cigarettes. This document is the subject of the Legal Times article entitled <a href="http://www.courttv.com/download/legalt.html">"Philip Morris v. ABC: The Tobacco Case ABC Never Made"</a> and the Associated Press article entitled "Legal Brief Says Philip Morris Adds Nicotine to Cigarettes." The brief is also the top "Editor's Picks" on <a href="http://www.counsel.com/lawlinks">Lawlinks</a></li> <li>1/96: <a href="http://www.gate.net/~jcannon/documents/wigand.html">Wigand Deposition</a></ul><p><li>4/2/96: The astounding anti-Dan Morales <a href="http://www.motherjones.com/mother_jones/MJ96/push_poll.html">push poll</a><li>Mother Jones has ABC's "Tobacco Under Fire," the 1994 documentary cancelled the day ABC was slapped with a multi-billion lawsuit by Philip Morris. <a href="http://www.motherjones.com">See MoJo's video clips</a><LI><A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/spotlight/tobacco/contents.htm">FDA Brief by Tobacco Companies</A> Brown & Williamson's Summary of Comments, Jan. 2, 1996--all 2,000 pages of it.</li><li><a href=http://www.tobacco.org/Documents/9511crsepa.html><strong>The CRS Report</strong> </a>  Nov. 14, 1995</strong>  <i> (75 pp--make sure your browser has lots of memory)</i></li><li>Study: Teens 3 times as sensitive to cigarette advertising than adults. <br><a href="http://www.ama.org/amanews/smokeweb.htm">Read the study </a> published in the April, 1996 <i> Journal of Marketing</i><li>CA Governor Pete Wilson is still "pro-tobacco," a lobbyist assures colleague. <a href="http://www.no-smoke.org/pm-wilsn.html"><br>Read the memo</a> released by <a href="http://www.no-smoke.org/">Americans for Non-smokers' Rights</a></ul><hr><a name = aastatistics><H3><a name=aa15>Statistics</a></H3></a><ul><li><a href="http://www.drugs.indiana.edu/drug_stats/home.html">Drug Statistics Home Page</a><p><li><a href="http://sunspot.health.org/forms/wsmoking.html">National Clearinghouse for Alcohol and Drug Information</a> (NCADI) Search Engine for a trove of study and statistics abstracts.<LI><A HREF="http://ssdc.ucsd.edu/ssdc/cps02.html">The Social Sciences Data Collection Census (SSDC) Enumeration at UCSD</A> is a collection of large numeric data files as well as a of computer programs that provide easy access to those data files through a menu interface. Although this version is still in development and data retrieval is not yet implemented, you are welcome to browse the catalog of study descriptions. It includes a description of Current Population Survey: Jan 1993, Tobacco Use Supplement.</li><UL><li><A HREF="http://www.cdc.gov/nchswww/hus-t63h.htm">CDC tobacco use page </A></li><LI><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/cgi-bin/includetext.pl?/General_Information/smoking/consumpt.txt">Cigarette Consumption - Statistics, per capita manufactures</a><LI> <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/cgi-bin/includetext.pl?/General_Information/smoking/statsovl.txt">Smoking by sex, race, type.  State Prevalence</a><LI><a href="http://www.cdc.gov/cgi-bin/includetext.pl?/General_Information/smoking/statsyth.txt">Smoking status of high school seniors</a>     <LI> <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/cgi-bin/includetext.pl?/General_Information/smoking/trends.txt">Smoking Tends overall, and by sex, race, age, education, current and former</a>     <LI><a href="http://oncolink.upenn.edu/cancer_news/cig_adult.html">Cigarette Smoking Among Adults</a> (OncoLink, UPENN) </UL>     <LI><A HREF="http://www.nih.gov" >U.S. National Institutes of Health (NIH)</A>      <li><A HREF="gopher://gopher.nhlbi.nih.gov">National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute Gopher</A></li><ul><li><a href="gopher://gopher.nhlbi.nih.gov/00/educprog/sea/pubs/public/smokiq.txt">NIH Smoking information</a> </li></ul><p><li><a href="http://www.bilkent.edu.tr/~Bilnews/doc1/1a.html">Smoking Statistics at Bilkrent</a> Turkey<hr></ul><a name = Newsgroups> <h2><a n