igarettes Home Page</A></li><p><li>9/96 Advertsing Issues (courtesy Larry Breed):<ul><li><a href="http://www.aig.org/aig/aig4.html ">The Advertising Information Group (AIG)</a> of England is troubled by tobacco control issues.<li><a href="http://www.awmanet.org/awma/category.html ">The American Wholesale Marketers Association (AWMA),</a> formerly the National Candy Wholesalers Association and the National Association of Tobacco Distributors, offers a list of 'Sixty-eight product categories presently are represented in the MarketPlus database', including many tobacco products. Within this organization, 'the average firm makes more than 2,000 deliveries per month and stamps more than 2,000 cases of cigarettes per month'.<li>For $25.00 you can (but I have not) purchase, <a href="http://www.realworks.com/ai/pubs/aipub006.htm ">The Appraisal of Outdoor Advertising Signs</a> by Donald T. Sutte, MAI. This book advertises itself with, 'The valuation of outdoor advertising signs requires knowledge of the locational and physical components of these unique properties and familiarity with the legal and political issues that surround them....and various court interpretations of government restrictions'.<li>Britain's main advertising lobby, the <strong>Advertising Association,</strong> addresses numerous advertising issues, including liquor, gambling, and <a href="http://www.adassoc.org.uk/aa/briefs/frames.html"> tobacco ad restrictions in the EU & UK</a></ul><li><a href="http://www.orge.ufl.edu/fyi/v23n07/fyi031.html"> Smokeless Tobacco Research Council - Grants-in-Aid</a>  From the University of Florida, Office of Research, Technology, & Graduate Education web site: <i>The Smokeless Tobacco Research Council, Inc. is continuing to sponsor independent research into questions of smokeless tobacco and health through a grants-in-aid program. Research that is aimed at elucidating the etiology and pathogenesis of diseases claimed to be associated with smokeless toba