om/specials/party_favors/database/default.asp">Follow the Money</a> Courtesy of MS/NBC's new site.<p><li><a href="http://www.contact.org">Contact Center Network </a> Newly revised. A treasure-trove of environmental/non-profit organizations listings. An emphasis on local orgs, with guides for taking community-based action.<li><a href="http://www.webdirectory.com/"> The Amazing Environmental Organization WebDirectory<li><a href="http://www.webactive.com"> Web Active</a> Very nice listing of activist orgs, including people trying to reform the PAC $$-dominated political system. Tobacco orgs are listed <a href="http://www.webactive.com/webactive/cgi-bin/wniasearch?tobacco"> here</a><li><A HREF="http://www.igc.org/fair">FAIR</A> </li><li><A HREF="http://www.cais.com:80/newtwatch/newt.html">Newt Watch</A> </li><li><a href="http://www.rnc.org/cgi-bin/platform.cgi">Advise the Republican National Committee on their platform</a> (Do so quickly; the platform will be set by the first week in August.) Volunteer at this site.<li><a href="http://www.democrats.org">Visit the Democratic National Committee</a> Volunteer at this site.<p><li><a href="http://www.democrats.org/college_democrats/buttman/"> Butt-Mania Online</a> Oh, those whacky collegiate Dems. Lots of info on Dole and tobacco, and a campaign to encourage him to "kick his nasty habit of taking huge contributions from the tobacco industry and the then acting as Big Tobacco's spokesman"<li>Keep up on the <a href="http://www.ca.cancer.org/prop99/"> Prop. 99 fight</a> courtesy ACS's California division</ul></ul><hr><h2><a name=aa33>INTERNATIONAL RESOURCES</a></h2><h3><a name=aa34>CANADIAN RESOURCES</a></h3><p><ul><LI><A HREF="http://hpb1.hwc.ca/">Health Canada</A></li><li><A HREF="http://fox.nstn.ca/~ncth2/ccshccts.html">Canadian Council on Smoking and Health</A></li><li><A HREF = "http://www.ccsh.ca/ncth">National Clearinghouse on Tobacco and Health </A></li> <UL><LI><a href=http://www.ccsh.ca/ncth