.html?query=tobacco+and+afco">The AFCO Case in 1988</a> (6/7/88), and more, including orders/judgements from: <br><ul> <a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/cgi-bin/sinodisp.pl/au/cases/cth/federal_ct/unrep3416.html?query=Tobacco+Institute+AND+Morling"> 10/21/88</a> <a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/cgi-bin/sinodisp.pl/au/cases/cth/federal_ct/unrep4971.html?query=Tobacco+Institute+AND+Morling">4/15/91</a> <a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/cgi-bin/sinodisp.pl/au/cases/cth/federal_ct/unrep4760.html?query=Tobacco+Institute+AND+Morling">4/15/91 (2)</a> <a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/cgi-bin/sinodisp.pl/au/cases/cth/federal_ct/unrep4982.html?query=Tobacco+Institute+AND+Morling">7/25/91</a></ul></ul><li><a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/legis/act/consol_act/ta192773/">Tobacco Act of 1927</a><li>All this is courtesy of the very aggressive and thorough <a href="http://www.austlii.edu.au/"> Australasian Legal Information Institute</a> Yes, "Australasian," with lots of international legal links. </ul>  </UL>  </UL></ul>	<hr><H2><a name=aa36>Useful Web Resources:</a></H2></center><br><i>These are not-strictly-tobacco-oriented-but-useful sites, some of which have kindly provided links to Tobacco BBS.<li><A href="http://www.amazon.com/">Amazon.com Books</a></i> 1 million books; if you need a book on tobacco, you'll likely find it here. Easy to search; join their personalized notification service for new books on the subject of your choice</li><li><a href="http://www.clearinghouse.net/">U. Mich. Clearinghouse</a>  Subject-Oriented Internet Resource Guides, i.e., webpages that feature a subject-specific compilation of sites--much as this page is dedicated to tobacco. The Clearinghouse has rated and organized them by subject matter over 400 of these guides to Internet Resources--including this page, which has been <strong> Clearinghouse approved</I></strong><li><A HREF = "http://www.mcp.com">New Riders' WWW Yellow Pages </A></li><HR><address><br>******