<p>NEW YORK OBSERVER</p>

<p>We Support Smoke-Free Restaurant Legislation</p>

<p>Smoke-Free Restaurants Will Let Us All Breathe Easier</p>

<p>Patrons and Restaurant Workers Alike!</p>

<p>Tobacco smoke is a Group A carcinogen. The U.S. government has determined that it causes cancer.</p>
<p>Neither patrons nor employees should have to breathe secondhand smoke. Waitresses suffer the highest lung cancer rate of any female occupation.</p>
<p>More than 100 dries have already passed smokeLree restaurant legishtion. Contrary to tobacco lobby propaganda, restaurants have not lost any business.</p>
<p>Zagat Survey reports that 70% of New York diners want all smoking banned in restaurants. ffNew York diners want it and scientists recommend it, then let's have it!</p>
<p>We appreciate all our customers and want to serve them the best possible food in the healthiest possible environment.</p>

<li>ARK RESTAURANT CORP.</li>
<li>85 5th Avenue</li>
<li>Manhattan</li>
