<br>
<br>
<!-------------------------------------------------------------->
The following audio clips are from President Reagan's remarks at National Review's 30th Anniversary party held<br> December 5, 1985 at the Plaza Hotel in New York City. We are making them available in two formats in order to accomodate those lacking a RealAudio Player, and also to satisfy visitors who are willing to wait for the higher<br>
quality sound of a WAV file to download.<P>
<P>
<center><img src="/nationalreview/images/reagan.gif" ALT="President Reagan on National Review"></center>
<blockquote>
<a href="reagan2.ram"><font size=+3>Why NR is my favorite </a>(148kb/ram)</font>
<P>
<a href="reagan1.ram"><font size=+3>A few words about WFB</a>(145kb/ram)</font>
<P>
<a href="reagan2.wav"><font size=+3>Why NR is my favorite</a> (848kb/wav)</font>
<P>
<a href="reagan1.wav"><font size=+3>A few words about WFB</a>(834kb/wav)</font
</center>





