<FONT SIZE=+1>BOOKS, ARTS & MANNERS</FONT>
<P><blockquote>
The Smelly Little Orthodoxies are coming to take George Orwell away. Not so fast, warns <b>Norman Podhoretz</b>....According to the title of David Brudnoy's memoir, <I>Life Is Not a Rehearsal</I>; yet an air of unreality pervades this book by a gay, AIDS-afflicted conservative who wishes that other conservatives would stop objecting to his life style. <b>Wm. F. Buckley Jr.</b> reflects....<b>John DiIulio Jr.</b> works over William Julius Wilson, the "thinking liberal" and author of <I>When Work Disappears: The World of the New Urban Poor</I>....A pretentious Australian film about the pianist David Helfgott, <I>Shine</I>, doesn't, regrets <b>John Simon</b>, who goes on to put <I>Evita</I> in <I>The Crucible</I> and finds her wanting....<b>Ralph de Toledano</b> wonders at <I>Wunderkinder</I>, notably Leila Josefowicz and Fr&eacuted&eacuteric Copin.  .
