<P><center>
<H2>Penn's State</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>



	"An outdoor display by the Penn State art department included a statue of the Virgin Mary resting within what appeared to be a grotto setting but which was actually female genitalia complete with surrounding pubic hair and emanating blood. When a priest from the Catholic campus ministry complained about this kitsch he was told the work was intended to bring attention to 'oppressed women in the church.' The 'artist' proved unable to explain what the placing of  a statue of Mary in this venue had to do with the oppression of women. While giving its blessing to what feminists celebrate as vaginal art, Penn State discourages nativity scenes as being contrary to the spirit of multiculturalism."
<P>
<I>Heterodoxy</I>, December 1996

</blockquote>
