<H2>Situations Available</H2>
<hr>
ATTORNEY. OPENING FOR a member of the bar to litigate in state and federal courts on behalf of employees challenging abuses of compulsory labor unionism. Litigation experience is desirable but not required. Outstanding law-school record is a requirement, and law-review experience is preferred. Strong commitment to the philosophy of individual freedom and free enterprise is necessary for success. The National Right to Work Legal Defense Foundation was established in 1968 to provide legal assistance to employees who suffer injustices concerning the collection and spending of forced union dues, union violence, hiring hall discrimination, and other abuses of coerced unionism. Applications, including a detailed resume, salary requirements, a legal writing sample, three references, and a transcript of law-school grades, should be directed to: Legal Director, National Right to Work Legal Defense Foundation, Suite 600, 8001 Braddock Road, Springfield, Virginia 22160. For further information on the Foundation and issues of law consult our Web site: http://www.nrtw.org.
<hr>
<P>
<H2>Vacation Rentals</H2>
<hr>
BEAUTIFULLY RESTORED COLONIAL INN located on easily accessible Loyalist Island of Green Turtle Cay, Bahamas. Has attracted celebrity guests of every description, including a former U.S. President (Republican, of course), but mostly caters to nice ordinary folks. 60% repeat clientele. $60 double occupancy. Includes English breakfast, delightful dinner. Information: Melissa Halsted, 908-735-4140 (phone/fax).
<hr>
MAUI -- IDYLLIC OCEANFRONT condo. One bedroom, fully furnished. $90 daily. 818-796-3451.
<HR>
<P>

<H2>T-Shirts & Bumper Stickers</H2>

<hr>
"DOWNSIZE GOVERNMENT EVERYWHERE..."; "STOP OVERGOVERNING!"; "IF IT DISTURBS THE PEACE...": Free bumper stickers. Dave Polewka, P.O. Box 3652, Chapel Hill, NC 27515-3652.
<hr>

<P>
<H2>For Sale</H2>

<hr>

SEIZED CARS FROM $175. Porsches, Cadillacs, Chevys, BMW, Corvettes. Also Jeeps, 4WD's. Your area. Toll free: 800-898-9778, Ext. A-3013 for current listings.
<HR>
<P>


<H2>Literary</H2>
<hr>
<center><b>$50,000 JOURNALISM FELLOWSHIP</b></center>
<P>
Working print journalists with less than five years' experience may apply for the 1997 Phillips Foundation Journalism Fellowship Program. One $50,000 full-time and two $25,000 part-time fellowships. Winners undertake a one-uear project of their choosing focusing on journalism supportive of American culture and a free society.
Application deadline March 1, 1997; fellowship commences September 2, 1997. Must be U.S. citizen.<br>
<b>Contact: John Farley, Phillips Foundation, 7811 Montrose Road, Potomac, MD 20854.</b> 
  
<hr>
<center><H3>NEW AUTHORS</H3><br>
<B>PUBLISH YOUR OWN WORK</B><br>
All subjects considered:<br>
Fiction, Biography, Poetry, Religion, Children's<br>
<I>AUTHORS WORLDWIDE INVITED<br>
Write, or send your manuscript to:</I><br>
<H3>MINERVA PRESS</H3><br>
2 Old Brompton Road, Lomdon SW7 3DQ England</center>
<HR>
GOOD USED BOOKS -- wide variety, intelligent selection. Libraries buy regularly; you can too. History, fiction, social science, literature, miscellaneous subjects. Send $2 for listings of 25,000 titles and prices. Editions, Desk NR, Boiceville, N.Y. 12412.
<hr>

